In fact, we can make our app even more flexible. If for example during development/testing we do not want to use secrets we can extend our app a little bit

#application.yml we extend by

```
# Properties
arctos:
  cold: ${ARCTOS_COLD:}

magic:
  value1: ${MAGIC_VALUE1:}
  value2: ${MAGIC_VALUE2:}
```

#docker-compose.yml we extend by

```
environment:
  MAGIC_VALUE1: &quot;env_used&quot;
  MAGIC_VALUE2: 0
  ARCTOS_COLD: &quot;In fact in env area is hot ;]&quot;
```

In such a case when secrets are not linked with our service the environment values are used. (In fact if you provide environment values they have precedence so finally anyway they win).

